               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. SLEIGH</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution</hi>:</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18481023-name-1297" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1297" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1297" type="surname" value="COLLEDGE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1297" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES COLLEDGE</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Amelia-street, Walworth-road, I hare been a beer-seller. On the night of 17th Oct., I went with the prisoners to the Fed Lion, and had some drink—they had been customers of mine—from there we went to the Blue Coat Boy, and had some drink, and from there to a house in East-lane—my wife came and asked me to go home—both prisoners want borne with me—Thomas went out with my wife and left Pingo and me—he struck me—that deprived me of my senses, and when I recovered I found my waistcoat opened and my watch gone—I said,. "Where is my wach?"—he said, "You have hid it"—I said, "No, I have not; you shall not go till it is found"—Thomas came in—I was then in the passage minding the loor—I said, "I have lost my watch"—Thomas said, "You have hid it</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184810230216"></xptr>
               <p>somewhere; I will go up stairs and find it"—she ran up stairs, got the watch and gave it me—the policeman came and said would I give them in charge—I said no, I had got my watch—I did not miss any money—I was not sober.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18481023-name-1298" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1298" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1298" type="surname" value="COLLEDGE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1298" type="given" value="MATILDA"></interp>MATILDA COLLEDGE</persName>
                  </hi>. I was passing by, and Pingo said, "Your husband is here with a lot of women; they won't allow us to drink with him," and they had sent for a woman to take his watch—he said, "I will see him home."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18481023-name-1299" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1299" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1299" type="surname" value="HALL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1299" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT HALL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a hairdresser, of 57, Amelia-street—Colledge lodges in my house. At half-past eleven o'clock on this night I heard a scuffle, and heard Colledge tell his wife in the passage that he had lost his gold watch—Thomas said she would find it—I said I would fetch a policeman.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18481023-name-1300" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1300" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1300" type="surname" value="LEECH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481023-name-1300" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN LEECH</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, P</hi> 139). I was called in, and found Colledge and his wife and the policeman up stairs—Colledge said he had lost his watch—Thomas said she had found it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. MELLER</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did not he say he had lost some money? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, 24<hi rend="italic">l</hi>., and there was 45<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. found in a pocket-book; and then he said he had lost 12<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. or 14<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.</p>
